  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThe [Constants](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/master/specs/core/0_beacon-chain.md#constants) section of the specification lists a set of \"constants\" that will define aspects of the Eth2.0 chain.\r\n\r\nAs far as the specification of a specific chain is concerned, these values are constant. However, from the perspective of Lighthouse these are configurable variables.\r\n\r\n## Task\r\n\r\nPresently there is a `ChainConfig` struct in `lighthouse/beacon_chain/types/src/chain_config.rs`. This is to be phased out, however removing it is not in the scope of this issue.\r\n\r\nFor this issue, create a new struct `ChainSpec` in `lighthouse/beacon_chain/types/src/chain_spec.rs` which includes all [Constants](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/master/specs/core/0_beacon-chain.md#constants) in the spec.\r\n",
